Kompera

THEMED ARMY LADDER COMPETITION

Rules

1. Your army must have one skill (weapons and equipment are skills) in common for all Troopers. Smart themed armies are excluded. Be sure to protect your army with a password so it stays that way! If your army cannot meet this condition it is disqualified from competition.

2. To join, place your Army Name, linked to your army URL, followed by your player name and a short note on the theme, at the bottom of the list of participants.

Example: Rocky III / Kompera - EotT

3. To move up the rank list, beat the person above you (using 'Infiltrate!' in the Pick a Fight section) and post the replay with the updated list.
It is possible to not realize you weren't at the last page, and use an old version of the list. If this happens, please edit your post to fix it! If you incorrectly fight an army which is not immediately above you in the ladder that fight is not counted.

4. You are responsible for the accuracy of your posts! If you screw up the order of the list and someone posts after you, your fights will be invalidated, not those of the person who went after you.

5. Each player can have up to four armies in the list. You don't fight your own army— you skip over them. All armies of the same player must have a different theme.

6. If you want to drop out of competition or replace one of your two armies with another, put [RETIRED] next to your retiring army in the list— also, strikethrough the link.

Example: Rocky III / Kompera [RETIRED]
Then if you wish you may add your new army at the bottom of the list.

[5379947]

Just a heads up, there's a length limit on posts, so it might be better to do the copy-paste URL thing like in continuous championship since every entry only takes one line (urls are auto-formatted), instead of the two used by "[link]" tags. Especially if everyone is entering multiple armies.

e.g. If you try to quote the CC ladder it adds [link] tags to each line and makes it twice as long. I was breaking my posts into two parts for like a week before I figured out I needed to copy-paste instead of quote

Kompera

Rocky III vs. Jacob's Ladder

I'm not sure this ladder is showing which skills are better. I think this ladder is proving that numbers are pretty important. Even armies with great skills are losing to armies that just have more troopers.

Eye of the Tiger is a pretty marginal skill, when you consider that people usually choose weapons like the CK-Magellan, the Beretta, and the Minigun/Comanche for their accuracy. All EotT let's me do is coast by on less optimal weapons.

[4286389]
KomperaRocky III vs. Jacob's Ladder

I'm not sure this ladder is showing which skills are better. I think this ladder is proving that numbers are pretty important. Even armies with great skills are losing to armies that just have more troopers.

Eye of the Tiger is a pretty marginal skill, when you consider that people usually choose weapons like the CK-Magellan, the Beretta, and the Minigun/Comanche for their accuracy. All EotT let's me do is coast by on less optimal weapons.

I don't think it's 100% numbers. 1) Italian is a good spy and Chemical Bob is a kind of crappy spy, and 2) Rocky has a comms officer and Jacob's doesn't.

I know from playing Laser Tag that the aim bonus makes you very good for your level up to about level 8 or so, but then you start paying for it in vulnerability to sabotage and overall speed (unless you are lucky and it's Minitroopers, luck is everything )

On september 14, 2013
Kompera
FragileWait, do I need to beat all of the armies belonging to the same person?

Please read the rules, which are posted on the first page of this thread. There you will see, aside from other important rules, that each player can enter up to 4 armies, and that to advance you must beat the army immediately above your in the list, not just any army of a particular player.

The only armies you can skip over are your own.

This post is not a complete listing of the rules. Following the link to the first page, or just hitting the <-<- link, is the way to ensure that you understand the have read and understand the rules of this competition.
On september 14, 2013
